        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 29 at 10:27PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 1026 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Harvest, or 7 miles northwest of Madison, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Madison, Huntsville, French Mill, Marshall Space Flight Center,
Harvest, Holland Gin, Hazel Green, Capshaw, Ryland, and Elkmont.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
